    Good drinks while gambling
    Great midday drink service if you want to gamble (get free drinks) during nap time. $5 first tip and $3 each drinks get you a server every 15-20 minutes If you know nothing about gambling, a slot machine will say min xx credits or $XX. That is the minimum bet on the machine, even if it is a penny slot. Some machines allow you to switch games, often the game that is not the default one has lower limits. Then there are the number of lines you are playing, this is how you win. Some machines allow you to change this. Some of the older machines we have a low amount you can win, like $10 on a $0.01 line without a jackpot. These machines are more fun since they do a lot more small payouts and aren’t saving money for the big one. Find one of these machines that costs less than $0.25 minimum (play at least 9 lines, preferably just 9 lines since going up doesn’t dramatically increase your payout number of spins on 3 rows, it does increase your winnings when wilds hit, but I prefer frequent small wins for low cost),and after an hour you will have had 3-4 decent cocktails and likely within $5 of what you started with. I played mid casino acrossish from the red neon lips in a shop. Best part is the machines I liked were in a row so you can socialize. This doesn’t get you rich, but gets you drinks and is fun. Then you can always go and play the table games.
    Visited February 2024
    Traveled with family

Choose any other hotel on the strip
Jul 2024 • Family
We are staying for 4 nights and really regretting staying here. I have been to Vegas many times and stayed in a lot of the hotels on the strip, all of them have better service than this place.

Positives first, the view from the room is awesome and we have a terrace suite with fountain views of the Bellagio which is really nice, picture attached.

Hotel is located perfectly in the centre of the strip, great location to explore in either direction.

Tv has all the channels, you can connect to Netflix or stream if you want. Free WiFi in room and throughout the resort, is patchy in some areas though and doesn’t work on the balcony.

Now the negatives, and there are many, probably too many for me to list all of them.

We arrived after a 4 hour drive from Palm Springs, to a very long queue for check in. There is no recognition for being a Marriott Bonvoy customer at this hotel, we are gold elite but means nothing here at all.

Room itself is a good size, separate sitting area with long couch and seats and a big balcony. You have an iPad for room controls and to connect to guest services, except our one doesn’t work. Been promised it will be fixed, 2 days in and still no solution.

Headed down to the pool, turned away with “no pool towels so you can’t come in”. Never experienced that at any hotel anywhere in the world and we travel a lot. Not even an apology, very rude staff.

The room has a jetted tub, except of course our one doesn’t work. Called reception and they said we will send someone straight up, over an hour later and no one came. I decided to head down and speak to management about speak to someone about our experiences. Spoke to management who said “we have given you resort credit, what more would you like me to do”. My answer was a very simple I expect and would like things to work. She assured me they will get everything fixed. The pool is run by someone else and not the hotel, they will communicate my grievance to the pool manager, great.

Went out for dinner and came back late that evening, jetted tub has been fixed…or we thought it had. Throughout the night the jetted tub would turn itself on, meaning I have to wake up and turn it off, not a good nights sleep. 2 mins into using in the morning, and not working again. Received an early morning email from Guest Services Lead, saying sorry for inconvenience but it has all been fixed. Have replied to her saying it hasn’t and I now give up, no response yet.

Back to our room at 6pm having been out all day, room hasn’t been cleaned. Spoke to housekeeping, “your room is still on the list to be cleaned”. Again, a first for me at any hotel, definitely a supposed high end one.

Sitting by the pool when we have made it in, trying to get a drink is really difficult.

My honest advice, stay at any of the other 5 star hotels on the strip, and get the service you pay for. I have stayed in most of them and they are all better.
Written July 24, 2024
